that Black gets control of the dark squares in exchange for the pawn. The
engine claims a slight advantage for White but I had decent results with the
move in the early 2000s drawing against strong theoriticians Khalifman,
Bologan and Hracek. Despite my relative success, I changed my preferences
again and soon discarded 7...Qb6: I was not happy with the fact that White can
go 8. Bxf6 (instead of 8.Nb3) and force gxf6. Even though the resulting
position is playable for Black, it does not suit my taste.} (9... gxf6 $6 {
