1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bg5 e6 7. Qd2 a6 8.
O-O-O Be7 {Probably, it is slightly more accurate to go 8...Bd7} 9. f4 Bd7 10.
Nf3 {is the main line which I find slightly problematic for Black} b5 11. Bxf6
gxf6 12. f5 Qb6 13. Kb1 O-O-O {In 2012, I almost stopped playing the Rauzer
because I was facing this position quite a lot and experienced problems after
the plan with g3, Bh3... Occasionally, I would still go for the Rauzer when I
knew my opponent was not playing 6.Bg5} 14. Qh6 Kb8 15. Qh5 Be8 16. Qh3 Bd7 17.
Qh5 {I took the draw as it was a good result in my tournament situation} Be8
18. Qh3 Bd7 19. Qh5 1/2-1/2

