1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bc4 e6 7. Be3 a6 8. Qe2
Qc7 9. O-O-O Be7 10. Bb3 O-O 11. Rhg1 Nd7 {Is another typical idea for Black.
Black is maneuvering the knight without waiting for the g4-g5.} 12. g4 Nc5 13.
Nf5 $1 {In the previous game we checked the Nd5 idea, this time, we see
another typical sacrifice.} b5 14. Bd5 $1 {Another typical sacrifice. Usually,
White sacrifices the knight, but the bishop sacrifice is also typical} Bb7 ({
If Black accepts the sacrifice, then the g-file will be open and White will
have the d5-square at his proposal.} 14... exf5 $2 15. gxf5 $18) (14... exd5
15. Nxd5 $40) 15. g5 {All the time, accepting the sacrifice leads to a very
complicated position where White has more than enough initiative.} Rfc8 16. Rg3
$5 b4 17. Nxg7 $5 Kxg7 18. Qh5 Rg8 19. Bxe6 $5 bxc3 $2 {This is the final
mistake.} (19... Nxe6 $1 {Black is better after:} 20. Nd5 Qd8 $1 {White has
compensation, but probably not enough for the two pieces.}) 20. Bxf7 $1 $18 Qa5
21. Rh3 $1 Kf8 22. Rf3 $1 Ne5 23. Bd5+ Kg7 24. Rf7+ 1-0

