{The former Ukrainian lost the match but took his revenge in the very last
competition for the year by obtaining the World title in blitz. The following
flashy victory contributed a lot to his overall success:} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3.
d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bg5 e6 7. Qd2 a6 8. O-O-O h6 9. Nxc6 bxc6 10.
Bf4 d5 11. Qe3 Bb4 12. Be2 O-O 13. e5 Nd7 14. h4 c5 $6 {Diagram #} ({The
dangerous piece sacrifice had to be anticipated and} 14... f6 $1 $132 {looked
as the best way to proceed.}) 15. Bxh6 $1 gxh6 $2 ({here too} 15... f6 {
had to be preferred.}) 16. Qxh6 $18 {Natural and strong, although White could
choose 16.Rh3 with the same devastating effect. 16....} Nxe5 (16... Bxc3 {
Diagram #} 17. bxc3 Nxe5 (17... f5 18. Rd3 f4 19. Qxe6+ Kg7 20. Qxd5 Ra7 21. e6
) 18. Rh3 Bd7 (18... Ra7 {transposes to the game}) 19. Rdh1 $5 ({White could
bring a rook to g3 while keeping the other one on-file, also by} 19. Rdd3)
19... f5 (19... Qe7 20. Rg3+ Ng6 21. h5) 20. Rg3+ Ng4 21. Bxg4 Kf7 22. Bh5+ Ke7
23. c4 d4 $140 24. Re1 $18) (16... f5 17. Rh3 f4 18. Qxe6+ Kg7 19. Qg4+ Kh8 20.
Qh5+ Kg7 21. Nxd5 {Diagram # and the attack is irresistable even without the
queens, for example 21.....} Qe8 22. Qg5+ Qg6 23. Bd3 Qxg5 24. hxg5 Rf7 (24...
Rh8 25. Rxh8 Kxh8 26. e6 Ne5 27. Rh1+ Kg8 28. Nf6+ Kf8 29. Rh7 c4 30. g6) 25.
Rh7+ Kf8 26. Rxf7+ Kxf7 27. e6+ Kxe6 28. Nc7+ Kf7 29. Nxa8 $18) (16... Qc7 17.
Qg5+ Kh8 18. Rd3 Qxe5 19. Qh6+ Kg8 20. Rhh3 $1 f5 21. Rhg3+ Kf7 22. Rde3 $18) (
16... Re8 $6 17. Rh3 Nxe5 18. Ne4 $18) 17. Rh3 Bxc3 18. bxc3 Ra7 19. Rg3+ Ng6
20. h5 ({or the immediate} 20. Bd3 $18) 20... Qh4 21. Rg4 Qh2 22. Bd3 1-0

