{Ivanchuk must be himself happy with his own triumph in the rapid event.
Several days earlier he was lucky to survive in a similar position from the
same opening. Diagram #} 12. a3 Ba5 13. f3 O-O 14. e5 Nh5 15. Bxh6 gxh6 16.
Qxh6 Ng7 17. Bd3 (17. Ne4 {could be nicely refuted by 17....} Nf5 18. Nf6+ Qxf6
$1) 17... f5 18. g4 {the diagonal had just been blocked, so opening a file was
a logical idea. 18....} Bxc3 $6 {Diagram #} ({Once they jump to e4 was no
longer a threat, then Black could keep the bishop for controlling the
g1-square -} 18... Bb6 $1 19. gxf5 $140 exf5 20. Qxc6 Be6 {with a promising
position.}) 19. bxc3 Ra7 20. Rhg1 Qa5 21. gxf5 exf5 22. Kd2 Rd8 23. Rg5 (23.
Rg3 $142 d4 24. Bc4+ Rd5 25. Qxc6 Qxc3+ $140 26. Ke2 $18) 23... d4 24. Bc4+ Rd5
25. Qxc6 $4 {Diagram # A heavy mistake.} (25. Bxd5+ cxd5 26. Qc6 {with clear
advantage.}) 25... Qxc3+ 26. Ke2 Qe3+ 27. Kf1 Qxf3+ 28. Ke1 Qe3+ 29. Kf1 Qf4+
30. Kg2 Qxg5+ 31. Kh1 Bb7 32. Bxd5+ Kh7 33. Qc5 Bxd5+ 34. Qxd5 Rc7 35. Rg1 Qf4
36. Qd6 Qe4+ 37. Rg2 Rc6 0-1

