{[#] What is the best plan for Black?} 16... Ne8 $3 {[%cal Ge8c7,Gc7b5] A very
instructive great idea. Black plans to transfer his knight to b5 to utilize
the weakness of the c3-pawn.} 17. Qf2 {After this prophylactical move, White
has taken a precaution against Nc7-Nb5 by planning to respond ...Nc7 with Bb6.}
(17. Bc4 $2 {is a mistake and after} Qa5 {[%csl Ra2]} 18. Kb1 Nc7 $17 {[%cal
Gc7b5] There is no way to prevent ...Nb5. Black is better.}) 17... a5 18. Bc4 (
18. Nc4 Be6 19. Kb1 Nc7 20. Bb6 (20. Nxa5 $6 {is dubious because after} Qd7 $17
{[%cal Gf8c8,Gc7b5] Black wants to play ...Rfc8, ...Nb5. Black's position is
clearly better.}) 20... a4 $15 {Black has excellent prospects.}) 18... Nc7 {
[%cal Gc7b5] Black wants to play ...Nb5 and of course White should not allow
it.} 19. Bb6 Bg5+ 20. Kb1 Rxb6 $1 {With this nice tactical idea, the game ends
in a very aesthetical draw.} 21. Qxb6 Nb5 22. Qxd8 Na3+ 23. Ka1 Nxc2+ 24. Kb1
Na3+ $11 {Draw by perpetual check.} *

