{[#] White is threatening to play Bxf6 and e5. How can Black prevent it and
take the initiative?} 16... Nxe4 $1 {We should not forget this tactical idea
we have seen before. We can face this idea in many positions. In this position
Black gets an edge thanks to this idea.} 17. Qxe4 d5 18. Qd3 (18. Qe3 $6 dxc4
19. Bxg7 Kxg7 20. Rxd8 Rfxd8 $17 {[%csl Rb3] After Black takes the white
bishop on b3, it will be rook and two bishops against the queen. This material
balance is very advantageous for Black.}) 18... Bf6 19. Bxf6 Qxf6 20. Qd4 dxc4
21. Bxc4 Bxc4 22. Qxc4 a5 $15 {Black's position is very comfortable and
slightly better.} *

