{[#] On the last move, White played 11.Bg5. This is a mistake. What is Black's
best response?} 11... Nxe4 $1 {After this strong move Black has the advantage.}
12. Nxe4 (12. Bxe7 $6 Nxc3 13. Bxd8 Nxd1 14. Bc7 Nxb2 15. Bxd6 Rfd8 16. Bc5 Nb4
$17 {Black is a pawn up and he has a big advantage.}) 12... Bxg5 13. Qxd6 Be7
14. Qxd8 Rfxd8 15. Nec5 Bf5 $15 {[%csl Ge7,Gf5] Due to the bishop pair Black
is slightly better.} *

