{[#] White wants to control the d5-square and the light squares in general by
playing Bc4. How can Black prevent this?} 10... Ne7 $1 $146 {Very strong
novelty. Black prevents White's plan by immediately fighting for control of d5.
} 11. Bc4 (11. c4 Nxd5 12. cxd5 Bd7 13. Bd3 Qa5+ 14. Qd2 Bd8 $15 {[%csl Gd7,
Gd8] Black has a strong bishop pair and a very nice advantage.}) (11. Nxf6+
gxf6 12. Bb5+ Kf8 $1 13. Qd2 Kg7 14. O-O-O Qb6 15. Qxd6 Qxb5 16. Qxe7 Rac8 $36
{White is a pawn up but Black has a very strong initiative.}) 11... Bxd5 12.
Bxd5 Qa5+ 13. c3 Nxd5 14. Qxd5 Qxd5 15. exd5 Rc8 $15 {[%cal Ge8d7,Gc8c5] Black
will continue with ...Rc5, ... Kd7, etc. The endgame is very pleasant for
Black.} *

